org.geekden.servoy.ptk
Class AbstractScriptObject

java.lang.Object
  org.geekden.servoy.ptk.AbstractScriptObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
IScriptObject
public abstract class AbstractScriptObject
extends Object
implements IScriptObject

Provides an IScriptObject implementation that relies on a simple annotation to export methods. To use, extend this class, define public method(s) with the "js_" prefix (as required by Servoy) and annotate them with the Export annotation. To mark a script method as being deprecated use the standard Java (1.5+) Deprecated annotation.

For example: 

 public class HelloWorldScriptObject extends AbstractScriptObject
 {
   @Export(
     parameters = { "message" },
     tooltip = "Hello World",
     sample = "plugins.ex.hello('World!');") 
   public void js_hello(String message)
   {
     System.out.println("Hello " + message);
   }
   
   // this less-sophisticated method is now deprecated...
   @Export @Deprecated 
   public void js_helloWorld()
   {
     System.out.println("Hello World!");
   }
 }
